HEADWORD: Bulker
<hw>Bulk"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
person employed to ascertain the bulk or size of goods, in order to fix
the amount of freight or dues payable on them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

